  "doc_id": "6077",
  "text": "South African Department of Health guidelines call for lopinavir/ritonavir after an NNRTI regimen failure in adults and for first-line lopinavir/ritonavir in children, who are often exposed to the NNRTI nevirapine during or after birth. PI-related mutations are rare during early failure of a ritonavir-boosted PI in adults [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and older children [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , but they have been detected in children previously exposed to PIs [CITATION_5] .",
